# Ops (@Ops)

## Stack

- **Compose files:** `backend/docker/docker-compose.yml` (project **`litecoin-ordinals-dev`**) and `test-docker-compose.yml` (**`litecoin-ordinals-test`**). Do not rely on the implicit folder name `docker` as the project name.
- **Postgres host port** defaults to **`15432`** (`EXPLORER_POSTGRES_PORT` in `backend/docker/.env`). **`DATABASE_URL`** in `backend/.env` must be a full URL (`postgresql://user:pass@127.0.0.1:<port>/db`) matching that port.
- **Litecoin + ord (two profiles):**
  - **`litecoin-mainnet`** (default for production-like work): **`litecoind-mainnet`** (RPC **9332**, IBD first) → **`ord-litecoin-mainnet`** (HTTP **8081**). Start node, let sync advance, then ord — see root **`MISSION_CONTROL.md`**.
  - **`litecoin`**: **regtest** + ord on **8080** / RPC **19443** for fast local iteration.
  - **BTCPay:** `backend/docker/btcpay/README.md`.

## Commands

All **`docker compose`** examples assume **repository root** as cwd (or use the wrapper).

### Wrapper (preferred)

- **`bash scripts/docker-explorer-compose.sh up -d postgres`** — dev DB only.
- **`bash scripts/docker-explorer-compose.sh --profile litecoin-mainnet up -d litecoind-mainnet`** — mainnet node only (IBD).
- **`bash scripts/docker-explorer-compose.sh --profile litecoin-mainnet up -d ord-litecoin-mainnet`** — start **ord** after the node is up (same profile; builds/pulls image if needed).
- **`bash scripts/docker-explorer-compose.sh --profile litecoin-mainnet up -d --build`** — Postgres + mainnet node + ord (ord waits on node healthcheck; first ord build can take minutes).
- **`bash scripts/docker-explorer-compose.sh --profile litecoin up -d --build`** — regtest **`litecoind`** + **`ord-litecoin`** (**8080**).

### Raw `docker compose` (equivalent)

```bash
docker compose -f backend/docker/docker-compose.yml up -d postgres
docker compose -f backend/docker/docker-compose.yml --profile litecoin-mainnet up -d litecoind-mainnet
docker compose -f backend/docker/docker-compose.yml --profile litecoin-mainnet up -d ord-litecoin-mainnet
docker compose -f backend/docker/docker-compose.yml --profile litecoin-mainnet up -d --build
docker compose -f backend/docker/docker-compose.yml --profile litecoin up -d --build
```

### Handy

- **Recreate mainnet node:** add **`--force-recreate litecoind-mainnet`** to the same `up` line.
- **Logs:** `docker compose -f backend/docker/docker-compose.yml logs -f litecoind-mainnet` or **`ord-litecoin-mainnet`**.
- **`scripts/health-check.sh`** / **`verify-inscription-gate.sh`** load **`backend/docker/.env`** when present so the DB port matches compose; for the gate, set **`ORD_LITECOIN_URL`** (e.g. **8081** mainnet ord, **8080** regtest).

## Secrets

- No real passwords or webhook secrets in git; use gitignored **`.env`** files.

## CI

- Run health + verify scripts when DB and ord are available; otherwise at least **`npx prisma validate`** in `backend/`.
